<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,261,1556]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,1493,1519]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet, 
<emphasis box="[637,698,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">furca</emphasis>
, a Latin noun meaning fork, refers to the characteristic emargination of the female ventrite 5.
</paragraph>
